caption: Quick service. Nice staff
It's Dunkin donuts. 🤷

There are three ladies that work in the morning that are great. They are always pleasant. I went this afternoon 2/1 in the heavy snow and there was a man which I assume is the manager. At first he was pleasant , but I had a minor complaint about the coffee I had. I asked for a midnight and he gave me regular. When I tried to correct him , his pleasant nature turned into an aggressive one. He asked if I want regular and I said No , I would like midnight and the one I had was not midnight  (Not to mention the coffee was like warm) He told me with an aggressive attitude "hurry up, I have customers. " I asked for my money back in a polite manner right away because I paid for a midnight coffee so I expect to get what I asked for , if what I ask for can not be accommodated then say that. Good customer service should be a priority, especially if the customer has not presented with an aggressive attitude. If I was rude then I could understand from the receiving end.

This staff and service is deplorable. I am from out of state and stopped in to order a personalized cake for my daughter’s birthday. 2 days later the cake was supposed to be ready. Upon arrival of picking up the cake, I was told the cake decorator never showed. They didn’t even have the decency to inform me ahead of time and felt that they compensated for the inconvenience by trying to force me to take some other cake that my daughter would not like. Now, a week later I still have not been refunded after being promised a refund within 24 hours.

From the outside looking in it look like a Dunkin Donuts location. Going in I noticed they were slow but the place was not clean like garbage and etc were an bit overflowing but it look manageable. The reason the place was slow and not 100% clean was perhaps the staff was only 2 people. Well when I ordered a ice cold brew with sugar free hazelnut cream and two splenda with pumpkin munchkins. The order itself was good but communication was off. When I ordered my coffee, the lady behind the register was having hard time understanding me. I understand that English may not be her primary language but when you are behind the register you going to take English words of coffee and DD menu of items. So it should be help for the manager to also teach her more English so she can succeed at her job but also teach her the menu and hire more people so she doesn't get flustered and be the only one. I was patient and understanding but I don't know if others will. Kudos to the manager on duty helping her and being extremely patient with her. Hopefully you guys will be master of Baristas making DD awesome! Ice coffee was brewed cold and delicious.

The unit was clean and opened for business during early morning hours. The young man on shift behind the counter delivered excellent customer service. He'd eben went above and beyond to explain to me the ingredients in the coffee that I picked and had questions about. Since I'm not a frequent customer I had questions about what was on the selection. The young man was professional and kind enough to share information about what I had inquiries about. I felt welcomed considering this type of service is rare to find throughout NYC and the neighboring boroughs. I believe this is a direct reflection of what Dunkin Doughnut as a company is doing to hire and train employees to produce such a high level of customer service. This caliber of service is what customer want. On behalf of myself and other customers that appreciate such service, we really appreciate it. (Upper management needs to recognize this young man: he works the early shift from which I believe I bought my coffee at approx 05:45 July 12th 2019. He had an interesting hairstyle with blond die on top/ Latino male approx early 20s) investing in employees like this can guarantee the success of your company and the future. People that care...
